* Command Shells

** Primary Power User Tool

A Command Shell is an application which provides a simplified language
primarily oriented around running and controlling other programs,
including running multiple other programs in combination to solve
problems which would be beyond any one program to solve by itself.

Command shells leverage the fact that almost all computer applications
can be executed from a textual command, even if they are now more
commonly launched from a [[file:graphical-shells.org][]Graphical Shell]].

